#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:1
msgid "Code of Conduct Committee Governance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:3
msgid "Membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:5
msgid ""
"Any voting member of the Carpentries community, as defined in The "
"Carpentries bylaws, may express their interest to volunteer to sit on the"
" Code of Conduct Committee (CoCc) (the Committee). The Committee will "
"onboard its members on a yearly basis through open calls and from "
"available volunteers. The Executive Council (EC) will be notified about "
"any new members. New members will undergo an application and onboarding "
"process before they are officially seated on the Committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:10
msgid "Onboarding and training"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:12
msgid ""
"The onboarding process is determined by the Committee, and the EC will be"
" notified about this process. New members are not immediately seated on "
"the Committee, and thus not included in issue resolution, until after "
"onboarding is completed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:15
msgid ""
"The current onboarding process involves reading assignments in The "
"Carpentries Code of Conduct documents and selected chapters from How to "
"respond to Code of Conduct Reports (by Valerie Aurora, based on a short "
"guide written by Mary Gardiner). Additionally, incident response training"
" will be organised for the new and existing members to ensure they can "
"confidently serve on the committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:19
msgid "Administration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:21
msgid ""
"The Committee consists of a minimum of five members; approximately 10 is "
"recommended. The Committee, in addition, has a liaison from the "
"Carpentries Core Team and a liaison from the EC. The liaisons have the "
"responsibility of informing the CoCc of anything that is relevant from "
"their respective groups. They are also responsible for conveying issues "
"and updates to their respective groups from the CoCc that are relevant "
"for them while respecting the confidentiality requirements of the "
"Committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:26
msgid ""
"The Committee has two chairs - a Governance Chair and an Incident "
"Response Chair. These individuals are responsible for guiding the "
"Committee’s work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:29
msgid "Voting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:31
msgid ""
"The CoCc participates in two types of voting - votes about incidents and "
"those not about incidents (e.g. business, policy, administrative "
"matters)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:33
msgid "Non-incident voting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:35
#, python-format
msgid ""
"For non-incident related matters, the Committee passes votes with a "
"simple majority of the non-liaison members, with the Governance Chair "
"breaking any ties. The Carpentries Core Team and Executive Council "
"liaisons do not vote on motions, but are welcome to provide feedback and "
"insight.<br />Quorum in meetings is more than 50% of the non-liaison CoCc"
" members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:39
msgid "Incident voting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:41
msgid ""
"For incident related matters, the liaisons to the CoCc will abstain from "
"voting, unless their vote is needed to ensure that an incident or other "
"need can be responded to in a timely manner according to the Incident "
"Response Guidelines. The Incidence Response Lead of the Incident Response"
" group will make this decision and indicate that a liaison vote will be "
"necessary to resolve the incident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:44
msgid ""
"Should the Executive Council liaison participate in a CoCc vote, and that"
" resolution is appealed before the Executive Council, the liaison member "
"will abstain from that appeal vote."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:46
msgid "Terms of office"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:48
msgid ""
"The expected term of office for each Committee member is one to three "
"years, however, members may remain longer if continuity of the Committee "
"is a concern. During their time on the Committee, members may temporarily"
" withdraw from Committee work for up to 3 months provided they inform the"
" Governance Chair in writing. If the members are unavailable for longer "
"than 3 months, they will be asked to take a leave from the Committee. "
"They may volunteer to rejoin when they are available again following the "
"onboarding procedure described earlier in the document. This will allow "
"us to maintain privacy for the reports that will be handled in their "
"absence and create an opportunity for new members to join the Committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:54
msgid ""
"The Chairs are expected to sit for approximately one year. New Chairs are"
" selected from among those who have been on the Committee for at least "
"one year. One of the available members can volunteer to be elected to "
"take on the role of a Chair."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:57
msgid "Main duties of the position holders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:59
msgid ""
"All members of the CoCc must read, understand and abide by the membership"
" agreement. In addition to the roles and responsibilities outlined in the"
" membership agreement (e.g. engaging in GitHub issues and reviewing "
"transparency reports), committee officers have the duties outlined below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:62
msgid "Chairs’ roles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:64
msgid ""
"The CoCc utilises two Chair positions, Governance Chair and Incident "
"Response Chair, who share leadership and operational responsibilities. "
"Both the Chairs will share the following responsibilities:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:65
msgid "Keep an overview of the ongoing work in the Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:66
msgid "Draft and review new policies with other members of the Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:67
msgid "Assign Committee related tasks to the Committee members fairly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:68
msgid ""
"Help and support other members in using tools and approaches effective "
"for the Committee’s work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:69
msgid ""
"Plan training scheduled for  Committee members and other stakeholders of "
"CoC enforcement on a yearly basis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:70
msgid "Communicate CoCc activities on via the Carpentries communications channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:72
msgid "Specific roles of the Governance Chair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:74
msgid "Schedule and chair business meetings quarterly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:75
msgid "Collect agenda points from Committee members for the business meetings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:76
msgid "Write, update, and maintain the business meeting minutes for the committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:77
msgid ""
"Co-edit and co-release transparency reports in collaboration with the EC "
"liaison and Committee members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:78
msgid ""
"Identify gaps in the current Code of Conduct, specifically governance, "
"and raise them to the Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:80
msgid "Specific roles of Incident Response Chair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:82
msgid "Monitor channels where the CoCc receives incident reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:83
msgid ""
"Organise incident response meetings for any new CoC incident report, and"
"   establish the Incident Response Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:84
msgid ""
"Support the Incident Response Group in documenting the incident -handling"
" process, and in coordination with the Governance Chair, assist the "
"Incident Response Group in communicating with the reporter and reportee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:85
msgid ""
"Identify gaps in the current Code of Conduct, specifically in the "
"incident reporting and incident-handling aspects, and raise them to the "
"Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:87
msgid "Core Team Liaison"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:89
msgid "Represent the CoCc in any relevant communication with the Core Team"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:90
msgid "Relay information to the Core Team members when required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:91
msgid ""
"Intervene in any communication or potential incident in Carpentries "
"online spaces that may lead to a CoC incident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:92
msgid ""
"Notify and request a review from the Carpentries Executive Director "
"regarding any public communication from the CoCc, when needed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:94
msgid "EC Liaison"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:96
msgid "Represent the CoCc in any relevant communication with the EC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:97
msgid "Relay information to the EC members when required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:98
msgid ""
"Co-edit and co-release transparency reports with the Incident Response "
"Chair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:99
msgid ""
"Notify, and request a review if needed, from EC regarding any public "
"communication from CoC committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:101
msgid "Incident Response Group’s roles and responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:103
msgid ""
"An Incident Response Group of a minimum of 3 people are convened for any "
"reported incident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:104
msgid ""
"An Incident Response Lead is selected in the Incident Response Group to "
"ensure accountability of the report handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:105
msgid ""
"The Core Team liaison will create a collaborative document for each case "
"and share with the Incident Response Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:106
msgid ""
"A note-taker will ensure that the notes are maintained for the Incident "
"Response Group and shared with the Code of Conduct committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-governance.md:107
msgid ""
"A time-keeper will notify the Incident Response Group of the various "
"deadlines"
msgstr ""

